Headline: ‘House of the Dragon’ to End With Season 4, Season 3 to End.
Summary: House of the Dragon season 3 will begin filming in 2025, according to showrunner Ryan Condal. The Game of Thrones prequel will end with Season 4. The series is based on a few chapters of House Targaryen lore in the fictional "history book" Fire & Ice. The Hedge Knight is set less than 100 years before GoT and chronicle the legend of "Dunk and Egg " The most recent announcement was that 10,000 Ships, a series set roughly 1,000 years before the events of GoT, is still in development. The writing process has already begun with the intention of doing prep in the fall. The returning cast includes Emma D’Arcy as Rhaenyra Targariesen, Olivia Cooke as Alicent Hightower and Tom Taylor as Lord Cregan Stark.

Headline: Zac Efron is ‘happy and healthy’ after recovering from swimming.
Summary: Zac Efron was taken to the hospital on Friday, August 2, after a "minor swimming incident," according to reports. The actor, 36, was found in the swimming pool by two employees at the villa who pulled him out of the water, according to TMZ. The Iron Claw actor was released from the hospital the following day. He has since shared a workout photo to assure fans that he's OK. He will next appear in Three Men and a Baby, a remake of the 1987 film, and the thriller Famous, which is currently in preproduction.Zac Efron was taken to a hospital in Ibiza, Spain, on Friday for a “minor swimming incident” The actor was discharged Saturday morning and was said to be doing “fine ” TMZ reported he was pulled out of a pool by two people working at a villa. The High School Musical alum was released from the hospital on Saturday morning. Zac will appear in Three Men and a Baby, a remake of the 1987 film, and the thriller Famous — both of which are currently in pre-production.

Headline: Ben Affleck is holding back on filing for divorce to ‘protect her’.
Summary: The couple have stopped talking altogether - making it even more difficult for the pair to reach an agreement. Lopez and Affleck rekindled their relationship in July 2021, following Lopez’s split from her former fiancé, Alex Rodriguez, in April 2021. The pair eloped in Las Vegas in July 2022, and had another wedding celebration at Affleck's home in Riceboro, Georgia, the next month. The couple finalized the divorce papers with her a month ago, but are waiting for the right time to drop them. A body language expert previously revealed that Ben and Jennifer appeared to be 'unhappy' and no longer have a 'look of love' in their eyes. Josh Shapiro is the betting favorite to be Vice President Kamala Harris’ running mate. Half of respondents believe the selection should be a male and about the same amount said he should hail from a swing state.

Headline: Ryan Gosling and Eva Mendes attend the 2024 Paris Olympics in a rare public outing.
Summary: The couple attended the women’s artistic gymnastics uneven bar finals at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games. They were joined by their two daughters, Esmeralda, 9, and Amada, 8, who haven’t been seen out in years. The Paris Olympics attracted numerous other high-profile celebrities, including Sharon Stone, Kendall Jenner, Pau Gasol and his wife, Ariana Grande. Lady Gaga and Tom Cruise were spotted sharing a warm embrace at Bercy Arena, where they came to support gymnast Simone Biles. The couple welcomed their daughters in 2014 and 2016, respectively, as they tend to keep their family out of the spotlight. The trip to Paris was a rare outing for the couple, who have largely kept their years-long romance out of public eye since its inception. The pair rarely post about each other online, or share much about their relationship with the public.

Headline: Shawn Levy on cameos and box-office success. 'Deadpool & Wolverine'.
Summary: "Deadpool & Wolverine" grossed a cumulative total of $395 6 million domestically and $824 1 million globally after just two weeks in movie theaters. "I'm really convinced there's too much about this movie that feels destined or at the very least informed by good karma," says director Ryan Reynolds. The movie has become a huge box office success since its release, taking over $590 million globally. It earned the biggest opening weekend ever for an R-rated movie, as well as the sixth best opening ever in the US. The film is expected to gross between $350 million and $390 million worldwide after its first weekend. It's expected to become the first in three years to surpass a billion dollars at the box office. The psychological thriller Never Lie tells the story of newlyweds Tricia and Ethan, who are on the hunt for their dream house.

Headline: Billy Ray Cyrus divorce is finalized; singer accuses ex of putting him in 'physical danger'
Summary: Billy Ray Cyrus and ex-wife Firerose have finalized their divorce three months after the country star petitioned for an annulment. Neither party was awarded alimony, and both parties agreed there are no jointly listed retirement assets. Cyrus and Firerose announced their engagement in November 2022 and married on his ranch on Oct 10, 2023. The Australian singer, 35, will get $0 from her ex but Cyrus, 62, will hand over his claims to credits and royalties for songs they wrote and published together. Billy Ray's rep said, "Mr  Cyrus is relieved to put this nightmare behind him"Cyrus filed to dissolve their seven-month marriage due to “irreconcilable differences and inappropriate marital conduct ” Cyrus accused Firerose of racking up a $96,986 bill between May 23 and June 7 on his American Express card. Court documents filed on Monday and obtained by DailyMail com reveal Firerose – who married the singer in October – walked away with $0 in the divorce. Billy Ray has agreed to hand over any claims he has to credits or royalties on songs that the couple wrote or published together before and during their marriage.

Headline: ‘John Wick 4’ Sequel Series From Keanu Reeves & Chad Staples.
Summary: A new series titled John Wick: Under The High Table is currently in the works from writer Robert Levine and director Chad Stahelski. Reeves is attached as an executive producer with no acting component with the project, which is being shopped in what is shaping up to become a competitive situation. The story picks up directly after the end of John Wick; Chapter 4 and a collection of new characters will look to make a name for themselves. Last year's John Wick 4 earned more than $440 million worldwide at the box office and pushed the series past the billion-dollar mark. Other projects in this universe are the Ana de Armas-led film Ballerina, plus a spinoff featuring Donnie Yen’s character, Caine. There is no release date or rough release window for the spinoff just yet.

Headline: LAPD releases images of suspects, vehicle in killing of 'General Hospital' actor Johnny.
Summary: Johnny Wactor, 37, was fatally shot on Saturday, May 25, in downtown Los Angeles. Police have released images of three suspects and the getaway car used in the killing. Wactor was best known for his General Hospital role as Brando Corbin. He also appeared in Army Wives, NCIS, The OA, Westworld, The Passenger, Station 19, Barbee Rehab, Siberia, Agent X, Vantastic, Animal Kingdom, Hollywood Girl and Training Day. He was shot in the chest by a mask-wearing suspect, his mother said.Johnny Wactor, 37, who played Brando Corbin on the ABC soap opera, was killed around 3:20 a m on May 25. LAPD said they had come across a group who were trying to steal a catalytic converter from the actor’s car. One of the group shot him and he was pronounced dead at an area hospital. Wactor appeared on nearly 200 episodes of "General Hospital" from 2020-22. His other credits included "Westworld," "The OA," "NCIS," "Station 19" and "Criminal Minds"Johnny Wactor, 37, was fatally shot on May 25 in downtown Los Angeles. Cops said Wactor was shot in the chest “without provocation” after he confronted the men who were in the process of stealing his car’s catalytic converter. The suspects fled the scene in a stolen 2018 four-door black Infiniti Q50 with a tan-colored interior. Wactor played Brando Corbin on the daytime soap opera, General Hospital and also appeared on shows including "Westworld, "NCIS" and "Criminal Minds"

Headline: Kanye West and Ty Dolla $ign Release New Album Vultures 2.
Summary: Kanye West and Ty Dolla $ign's Vultures 2 has 16 tracks in total with features from some frequent collaborators. The album remains a “living, breathing” body of work-in-progress with Ye and Ty still making updates to the sequel in real time. If Vulture 2 debuts atop the Billboard 200, Ye will have earned his 12th project to reach the chart’s apex in his career."Vultures Listening Experience” will take place Friday at the Delta Center, 301 W  South Temple, Salt Lake City.Kanye West and Ty Dolla $ign surprised fans with their spontaneous release of their latest album, Vultures 2. Portishead’s Geoff Barrow was annoyed to learned that the duo sampled the group's song “Machine Gun” without permission. The English producer and Beak> member posted a clip of the track on X (formerly Twitter) Barrow called out the duo for featuring its revered instrumental break on “Field Trip,” which features Playboi Carti, Don Toliver, and Kodak Black.

Headline: Prince Harry and Meghan Markle launch Parents' Network to address the dangers of online.
Summary: The Parents' Network is a group of parents who have lost children to internet harm. The group will meet mostly online, but will share stories of their own loss. Meghan said, "If me voicing what I have overcome will save someone, or encourage someone in their life to really genuinely check in on them, then that's worth it" The initiative is available on more than 30 platforms across mobile, desktop and connected TVs for free. It is now available for the first time for parents to join in the US, UK and Canada. It aims to support those whose children are struggling with 'present-day issues of cyberbullying, depression and anxiety, sexual exploitation, eating disorders, and a range of other traumas related to social media use' The campaign, which carries the slogan #NoChildLostToSocialMedia, features parents who lost their children to suicide because of online harm.
